bib_record.title: Measurement of neutron-capture cross sections of 70, 72Ge using the DANCE facility

free_txt: Measurements were conducted using 800
MeV proton beam at the Los Alamos Neutron Science
Center at Los Alamos National Laboratory.
Sample surrounded the array DANCE, consisting
of 160 BaF2 detectors covering almost 4Pi solid
angle. All detectors, firing within the 10-ns
coincidence window were considered to have detected
gamma rays from a single neutron capture event.

Measurements were conducted using 800
MeV proton beam at the Los Alamos Neutron Science
Center at Los Alamos National Laboratory.
Neutrons were produced by spallation of high
energy protons on tungsten target.
Time of flight was used for determination of
neutron energy. Proton beam was bunched into pulses
using a proton storage ring before being delivered to
a tungsten target where neutrons were produced by
high-energy spallation reactions. The neutrons were
moderated by a water moderator before impinging on a
sample located at a flight path length of 20.3 m
for En <= 5 keV
